## Context

Ticket 0288's BUILD phase landed the catalog_keydocs harvester, the merge/
filter/enrichment wiring, and curated STARTER seed lists (47 UNFCCC + 14 OECD
DAC entries in config/unfccc_sources.yaml and config/oecd_dac_sources.yaml).
The lists cover every document the manuscript cites (probe classes A/B/C) plus
the systematically enumerable series anchors, but the validated classes are
larger (UNFCCC order of magnitude 150-300), several entries carry provisional
symbols or empty URLs ("resolve at harvest" in provenance), and OECD One
returns 403 to robots so its PDFs need a manual bulk export.

Prerequisite: the 0288 BUILD PR (branch t288-corpus-v2-layer) must be merged.
This runs on/with padme: the full fetch sweep is a Phase-1 network operation,
coordinated with the author (data flows padme->doudou only).

## Relevant files

- `config/unfccc_sources.yaml`, `config/oecd_dac_sources.yaml` — seed lists to complete
- `scripts/harvest/catalog_keydocs.py` — harvester (metadata-only vs --fetch)
- `deliverables/data-paper/revision-rdj26561/biblio-vs-corpus-probe.md` — regression probe to rerun against corpus v2

## Actions

1. Enumerate the remaining documents within the author-validated classes,
   driven by a discovery script on the UNFCCC side (author decision,
   2026-07-22): unfccc.int/documents is a Drupal facet search with stable
   URL parameters (Topic="Climate finance" x Type=official documents/
   decisions x Body=SCF x Session/Year, verified 2026-07-22). Crawl it
   politely (pipeline_io.polite_get) to emit CANDIDATE entries as JSONL
   under data/ — teaching-style — then the author-validated candidates are
   appended to config/unfccc_sources.yaml, so the curation act stays a
   reviewable git diff. Coverage: full COP/CMP/CMA finance-decision series,
   all GCF/GEF/Adaptation Fund reports to COP/CMP, INC 1991-1995 session
   documents, party/bloc submissions sweep (NCQG, long-term finance), and
   ENB per-COP summaries (ENB lives on enb.iisd.org, not the UNFCCC portal
   — enumerate its own per-COP index, same candidates→validation flow).
2. Verify every provisional symbol and URL flagged "resolve/verify at
   harvest" in the seed provenance fields; fix titles to official form.
3. OECD: identify OLIS symbols for the 1998 Rio-marker directives and early
   DAC/WP-STAT/ENVIRONET documents; obtain PDFs via manual export where
   one.oecd.org blocks robots, pre-placing them in data/pool/keydocs/oecd/.
4. Run the full --fetch harvest on padme; check OCR coverage of pre-2007
   scanned material (ocrmypdf required on padme); review needs_ocr leftovers.
5. Rerun Phase 1 (make corpus on padme) and the bibliography-coverage probe:
   probe classes A and B must now match (regression check from 0288).

## Alignment with grey and teaching (design notes, 2026-07-22)

The layer reuses the repo's two existing seed idioms instead of inventing a
third; keep these alignments when building the discovery script:

- Discovery → candidates → validated YAML mirrors the teaching source
  (catalog_syllabi.py stages → build_teaching_yaml.py →
  data/teaching_sources.yaml): scripted-discovery output lands in data/
  (regenerable, DVC), validated seeds live in config/ (committed, curated) —
  the same split grey_sources.yaml already uses on the config side.
- Shared plumbing, no new framework: pipeline_io.polite_get for network,
  checkpointed/resumable stages a la syllabi if the crawl grows, pool caching
  as already wired in catalog_keydocs.
- Add a shared seed-YAML validation guard: one test sweeping
  config/*_sources.yaml for required fields, symbol/title uniqueness, and DOI
  polarity (grey entries MAY carry DOIs; keydocs entries MUST NOT — that
  polarity is the dedup boundary with the academic path).
- Explicit non-goals: do NOT merge catalog_grey and catalog_keydocs (different
  identifier regimes — DOI-joined + WB API vs symbol-joined curated — a common
  framework for three scripts is abstraction without payoff), and do NOT move
  grey's OECD-DOI seeds into the keydocs lists (the DOI polarity IS the
  boundary).

## Test

- Seed validation tests in tests/test_catalog_keydocs.py already gate list
  format; extend TestRealSeeds count floors as the lists grow.

## Verification

- [ ] No seed entry retains "resolve at harvest"/"to confirm at harvest" for symbol or URL
- [ ] Harvest run report: fetch/text status counts, zero unexplained failures
- [ ] Probe rerun against corpus v2: classes A and B matched

## Invariants

- Phase separation; in_v1 reproducibility; no one-shot manual dumps — every
  document enters via the seed lists + harvester.
- Small spot-fetches on doudou only; sweeps on padme.

## Exit criteria

- [ ] Both seed lists complete within the validated classes (UNFCCC ~150-300, OECD a few dozen)
- [ ] Full harvest completed on padme; unfccc_works.csv / oecd_works.csv populated
- [ ] Corpus v2 rebuilt with the layer present and correctly flagged (hands back to 0288 for counts/prose)
